name: Mariposa Food Co-Op
directions: Get the key from the cashier desk, bathroom is in the rear right corner of the store.
comment: Half the staff are trans and/or nonbinary including the top manager of the store, and even more are gay/bi/queer/etc. You will be very safe and welcome here, and security have been explicitly directed to deter any potential harassers that may give trans customers and staff a hard time.

name: Keltic Kitchen
directions: Two unisex restrooms to the right of the counter
comment: Only open 7-2(breakfast and lunch served all day)

name: Captain Parker's Pub
directions: Next to the mens room

name: Master’s Method Tattoo and Body Piercing
directions: The bathrooms is past the front desk. You can see the sign clearly from the entrance.
comment: Not entirely sure if you have to be a paying customer but the people who work there are allys.

name: Pilgrim Coffee Company
directions: At the back of the store

name: Moorhead Senior High
directions: Main floor, come in from door one and take a left into the closet hallway, on the left side of this hallway there will be a door with a sign outside of it reading "student assistance/security. Go through thw door. The bathroom is the second to your right.
comment: It's only open during school hours.

name: Staples
directions: Far right corner of the store. Two single stall, accessible, non-gendered washrooms.

name: J Petal Japanese Crepes
directions: For customers, two gender neutral restrooms in the rear

name: 601 Wabash St, Michigan City, IN 46360, USA
directions: right back side of the central visitors information building

name: Coronado Mall - Family bathroom outside Forever 21
directions: Go down the long hallway across from Forever 21 in the mall and you will find a family bathroom.

name: Kohl's - Family Bathroom
directions: 2nd floor of Kohl's has a family bathroom with an adult toilet and a cute little kiddie-sized toilet in one room that locks.

name: Starbucks - Unisex Bathrooms
directions: If you can't find the bathrooms inside Starbucks, I don't know how to help you.
comment: You don't have to be a paying customer but it's nice to show support for businesses.

name: Cinnamon Cafe
directions: Gendered single restrooms toward the back of the restaurant. Use women's if you need a changing table.
comment: You don't really HAVE to be a paying customer but it would help to at least look like you're planning to be one.

name: CNM Montoya Campus Library
directions: In the new library, down the hall toward the back of the library.
comment: You don't have to be a student to get into the library (at the time of this writing) but make sure you use guest parking, because other parking is paid.

name: Spin Cycle Coin Laundry of San Pedro
directions: One single stall restroom in the back left corner of the establishment
comment: Restroom is for customers only, but it's easy to get in when it's busy. Unfortunately, it's filthy.

name: Donauturm Observation Deck
directions: Use the (paid) elevator to get to the observation deck floor. There you can use the toilets which are all around the middle
comment: Paid Elevator Ride to get to the top (and therefore the toilets)

name: aburi house sushi and tepanyaki
comment: don’t think you need to be a customer to use the bathroom but the sushi is really yummy so you could always get some anyways ! :))

name: Ava Roasteria
directions: Down the hall to the right of the bar
comment: There's a code to the doors, ask a barista for it, they might ask you to buy something

name: 389 Ganttown Rd, Sewell, NJ 08080, USA
directions: the Italian restaurant

name: Homedepot, Santa Rosa
directions: To the right past self check out

name: Boynton Middle School
directions: one in nurse’s office or in the 8th grade science hallway
comment: (beware ms. shaup might be in the one in the science hallway) the principal doesn’t know if it’s for staff AND students so just use it anyway

name: Hangar Theater
directions: First floor near binary bathrooms

name: Hangar Theater
directions: near binary bathrooms to the right of the entrance

name: The Factory Theater
directions: Down the hall, through the door marked “restrooms”

name: Nordstrom
directions: First floor and on the right when you come in from the parking lot

name: Marcos Pizza
directions: Passed the seating area and the window to the hallway that goes to the back of the store.
comment: Not totally sure how trans friendly it is but both bathrooms are unisex and one is accessible. You do need to be a paying customer though.

name: Greko Greek Street Food

comment: Sign on front door reads: “we welcome all races, all religions, all countries of origin, all sexual orientations, all genders. We stand with you. You are safe here.”

name: On Point
directions: In the back on the right side corner.

name: Starbucks

name: Todo Mundo / Casa Ninja Lisboa

name: Bull’s Horn
directions: Go past the bar and take a left. Bathrooms in back on the left.

name: Seward Co-op Creamery
directions: Go past the counter and take a left. Bathrooms in the back on the right.
comment: The cafe has a policy about using gender neutral language when addressing staff.

name: Moon Palace
directions: Enter on Minnehaha, walk straight to the back. There is a doorway on the left near the back of the store that leads to three private ungendered bathrooms.

name: Kings Landing

name: Pizza Pizza

name: Victory auto
comment: Probably need to be a customer but it’s generally a friendly place. It’s been accredited by the better business bureau and they’re certified as ‘female friendly’ - less of the condescension and sleaziness one might expect from an auto shop.

name: Philadelphia’s magic gardens

name: 1600 Premium Outlets Blvd, Norfolk, VA 23502, USA

name: Allice

comment: Allice

name: Walmart

comment: across from the mezzanine entrance by the gym there are two gender neutral washrooms. The one on the left has two stalls and a sink and the one on the right has one stall, a sink, a changing area, and some lockers. They both can be locked from the inside and used as a change room for gym class.
